  </div>
  <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 testimony">
    <div class="message">
      <div class="pull-left image">
        <%= image_tag('joana.jpg') %>
      </div>
<p>      When I completed senior high school, I was so insecure and spiritually malnourished.
I knew about God but didn't know him personally. Deep down I knew there was something more than the 
  'shallow'Christian life I had been accustomed to. A friend convinced me to attend camp and that was the beginning of 
  my beautiful journey with God Youth Camp 2008 at Hephzibah Centre was my great awakening! 
  The atmosphere and environment was so welcoming and serene. My life took such a dramatic turn and I believe 
  the training I received from camp formed the moral and spiritual foundation that took me throughout my university education. 
  Since then, Youth Camp has been an encounter with God that I look forward every year. 
  Irrespective of your level of spiritual maturity, there is always something new to learn at Youth Camp.
Another remarkable testimony I had was at Youth Camp 2014 at PCC. I was so burdened with many worries during 
  that period of my life.
  I needed a job after national service and wanted my brother's interest in camp to be revived after 5 years of apathy.  
  There was a cross that was positioned at camp for prayer topics. In faith I wrote mine and stuck them to the cross. After camp,
  God came through for me in so many ways beyond my expectation.
  I was maintained permanently at work and given a better position!
  My brother also attended camp the following year and has never missed any of the subsequent sessions.
  God just 'wowed'me in so many ways.I would recommend Youth Camp for every believer who wants more of God, who would not 
  settle for the status quo and wants to leave a footprint in the sands of time! I promise you, your life would take a 180 degree turn. 
  Don't miss Youth Camp 2017!!

     <div class="name">Joana Hesse</div>
    </div>
    
     <div class="col-lg-6 col-md-6 testimony">
